# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OpenRecapper configuration. Copy to `.env` and fill in your own values.
# Each operator/fork must bring their OWN Discord app, Deepgram account, and
# (optionally) storage bucket + relay. No shared credentials are provided.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Required ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# From the Discord Developer Portal (see DISCORD_SETUP.md).
DISCORD_TOKEN=your-bot-token
DISCORD_CLIENT_ID=your-application-id
# Deepgram API key for speech-to-text (https://console.deepgram.com/).
DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=your-deepgram-api-key

# ── General (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Display name used in startup-alert DMs and email subjects.
BOT_NAME=OpenRecapper
# Where to write recordings on disk (defaults to ./recordings).
# RECORDINGS_DIR=/var/lib/openrecapper/recordings
# Discord user ID to DM if a startup health check fails (e.g. dead Deepgram key).
# ALERT_DISCORD_USER_ID=

# ── AI summaries & email (optional, via a relay service) ─────────────────────
# Summaries + email are produced by a small companion "relay" HTTP service that
# you run and point at your own LLM provider + email gateway. If RELAY_TOKEN is
# left blank the bot still records + transcribes; summaries/email are skipped.
# See README “AI summaries & email” for the expected relay API.
# RELAY_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8787
# RELAY_TOKEN=your-shared-relay-secret
# Model name passed through to your relay/LLM provider (blank = relay default).
# SUMMARY_MODEL=
# Tunes the summary template wording (e.g. "engineering standup", "book club").
# SUMMARY_GROUP_NAME=study group
# Email the summary + transcript links here after each call.
# SUMMARY_EMAIL_TO=you@example.com

# ── Cloud archival to S3-compatible storage (optional, e.g. Cloudflare R2) ────
# If these are unset, recordings/transcripts stay on local disk only. Upload is
# enabled when ACCESS_KEY_ID + SECRET_ACCESS_KEY + ENDPOINT are all present.
# R2_ACCOUNT_ID=
# R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# R2_BUCKET=your-bucket-name
# R2_ENDPOINT=https://<accountid>.r2.cloudflarestorage.com
# R2_PUBLIC_URL=https://your-public-bucket-url

# ── Scheduled recording (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Auto-join a voice channel on a cron schedule. All four are required together.
# SCHEDULED_GUILD_ID=
# SCHEDULED_VOICE_CHANNEL_ID=
# SCHEDULED_TEXT_CHANNEL_ID=
# SCHEDULED_CRON=15 11 * * 1,5
# SCHEDULED_TIMEZONE=America/New_York
